import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    ax = data['key'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Key')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of key values in the dataset?')
    for i in ax.patches:
        ax.text(i.get_x()+0.2, i.get_height()+1, str(i.get_height()), fontsize=10, color='black')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['lat'], vert=False, widths=0.7, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'))
    ax.set_title('What is the range of latitude values in the dataset?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_yticklabels([''])
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].min(), color='red', label=f'Min: {data["lat"].min():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].max(), color='green', label=f'Max: {data["lat"].max():.2f}')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(x=data['lat'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average latitude value in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Latitude")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['key'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='key', y='lat', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Key')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of latitude values for each key value in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
